&lt;p>Unchosen Forge: Viability Exercise Retro Graphics - Castleroid&lt;/p>
&lt;hr>
&lt;h3 id="tile-pallet-system">Tile Pallet System&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Work continues on my Castlevania 1 retro redux.  The Hall is coming along nicely.  Trying to focus on values, colors, and getting the tile system in place.  Much of the work isn&amp;rsquo;t shown in the simple graphic above, but I&amp;rsquo;m challenging myself to create a system that would theme of the environment to allow for a great deal more geometry.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Mecromage Foundational Assets</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/gamedev/mecromage/mecromage-foundational-assets/</link><pubDate>Tue, 08 Aug 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/gamedev/mecromage/mecromage-foundational-assets/</guid><description>&lt;h6 id="tilesscene04bpng-test-room-for-foundational-assets">TilesScene04b.png Test room for Foundational Assets&lt;/h6>
&lt;p>Foundational assets in Mecromage are the blueprint building blocks that indicate visual asset placement as well as game-mechanic specific objects.  They are designed to easily swap in and out to create Environment Themes.  They are instanced throughout the game in a way that allows them to be easily maintained.&lt;/p>
&lt;h6 id="2017-06-13-133921jpg-breakdown-of-wall-assets">2017-06-13 13.39.21.jpg Breakdown of wall assets&lt;/h6>
&lt;p>Deciding what and how these Foundational Assets would be, and importantly how they would be organized and maintained, has been no easy feat.  Clear communication of the needs of designers, artists, and programmars is essential.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Sprite In Progress</title><link>https://RaihnForge.github.io/gamedev/mecromage/sprite-in-progres/</link><pubDate>Sat, 04 Mar 2017 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://RaihnForge.github.io/gamedev/mecromage/sprite-in-progres/</guid><description>&lt;p>&lt;img src="https://RaihnForge.github.io/images/wp-imports/gamedev/sketchpad_turnaround.png" alt="sketchpad_turnaround">&lt;/p>
